<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1949-10-21T13:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1949-10-21T13:00:00-05:00" n="159" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d159">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">893.01/10–2149: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in the United Kingdom</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Holmes</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1949-10-21T19:00:00+01:00">October
                                    21, 1949—7 p. m.</date>
                                <lb/> [Received October 21—2:16 p. m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>4235. Embtel 4173, October 18. In further conversation with Dening this
                            afternoon he stated emphatically that Bevin–Acheson understanding
                            reached in Washington would include consultation in <pb facs="0150" n="140" xml:id="pg_140"/> advance regarding <hi rend="italic">de
                                facto</hi> as well <hi rend="italic">de jure</hi> recognition
                            Chinese Communists. Memorandum of conversation by air.<note n="43" xml:id="d159fn43">
                                <hi rend="italic">Supra.</hi>
                            </note>
                        </p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Holmes</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>